CodeClear.​NaturalDocs.​Engine.​Output.​Builders.​HTMLBuildState
public
CodeClear.​NaturalDocs.​Engine.​Output.​Builders.​HTMLBuildState

A class encompassing all the build state information for a HTML output target.

BuildState.nd

A file used to store the build state of this output target the last time it was built.

[Byte: Need to Build Frame Page (0 or 1)]
[Byte: Need to Build Main Style Files (0 or 1)]
[Byte: Need to Build Menu (0 or 1)]
[Byte: Need to Build Search Prefix Index (0 or 1)]

Flags for some of the structural items that need to be built.

[NumberSet: Source File IDs to Rebuild]
[NumberSet: Class IDs to Rebuild]
[NumberSet: Style File IDs to Rebuild]

The source and class files that needed to be rebuilt but weren't yet.  If the last build was run to completion these should be empty sets, though if the build was interrupted this will have the ones left to do.

[NumberSet: Source File IDs with Content]
[NumberSet: Class IDs with Content]

A set of all the source and class files known to have content after all filters were applied.

[StringSet: Search Prefixes to Rebuild]

A set of all the search index prefixes which were changed or deleted and thus need to be rebuilt.

[StringSet: Folders to Check for Deletion]

A set of all folders which have had files removed and thus should be removed if empty.  If the last build was run to completion this should be an empty set.

[String: Menu Data File Type] [NumberSet: Menu Data File Numbers]
[String: Menu Data File Type] [NumberSet: Menu Data File Numbers]
...
[String: null]

A list of the data files that were created to build the menu, stored as string-NumberSet pairs that repeats until there is a null string.  This allows us to clean up old data files if we're using fewer than before.

The type will be strings like "files" and "classes", so if the menu created files.js, files2.js, and files3.js, this will be stored as "files" and {1-3}.

Version History

  • 2.0.2

    • Added Style File IDs to Rebuild.

Functions
HTMLBuildState
public HTMLBuildState ()
HTMLBuildState
private HTMLBuildState (
bool createEmptyObjects
)

In this version of the constructor you can set createEmptyObjects to false to have variables like sourceFilesToRebuild set to null instead of empty objects.  Only do this if you're going to be creating the objects yourself since they shouldn't normally be set to null.

Properties
SourceFilesToRebuild
public IDObjects.NumberSet SourceFilesToRebuild { get }

A set of the source file IDs that need their output file rebuilt.

SourceFilesWithContent
public IDObjects.NumberSet SourceFilesWithContent { get }

A set of the source file IDs that contain content this output target can use.  This is different from all the files with content in CodeDB.Manager because it is after all filters have been applied.

ClassFilesToRebuild
public IDObjects.NumberSet ClassFilesToRebuild { get }

A set of the class IDs that need their output file rebuilt.

ClassFilesWithContent
public IDObjects.NumberSet ClassFilesWithContent { get }

A set of the class IDs that contain content this output target can use.  This is different from all the classes with content in CodeDB.Manager because it is after all filters have been applied.

StyleFilesToRebuild
public IDObjects.NumberSet StyleFilesToRebuild { get }

A set of IDs for the style files that need their output updated.  This includes new, changed, and deleted files so you should check the file's status to see if it's deleted before processing it.

NeedToBuildFramePage
public bool NeedToBuildFramePage { get; set }

Whether the frame page, index.html, needs to be rebuilt.

NeedToBuildMainStyleFiles
public bool NeedToBuildMainStyleFiles { get; set }

Whether the main style files, main.css and main.js, need to be rebuilt.

NeedToBuildMenu
public bool NeedToBuildMenu { get; set }

Whether the menu data files need to be rebuilt.

UsedMenuDataFiles
public StringTable<IDObjects.NumberSet> UsedMenuDataFiles { get; set }

The menu data files created the last time the menu was built.  It maps strings like "files" and "classes" to NumberSets, so files.js, files2.js, and files3.js would map to "files" and {1-3}.

NeedToBuildSearchPrefixIndex
public bool NeedToBuildSearchPrefixIndex { get; set }

Whether the search prefix index needs to be rebuilt.

SearchPrefixesToRebuild
public StringSet SearchPrefixesToRebuild { get }

A set of all the search index prefixes which need to be rebuilt.  This set combines changed and deleted IDs, so when using SearchIndex.Manager.GetKeywordEntries() make sure to test each result for null.

FoldersToCheckForDeletion
public StringSet FoldersToCheckForDeletion { get }

A set of folders that have had files removed, and thus should be deleted if empty.
